libnginx-mod-http-shapow (2.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Do not allow the usage of SHAPOW directives in if statements, since they
    were (predictably) not working as expected
  * Introduce variable support for the `shapow` directive as an alternative to
    if statements 
  * Add polyfills for some recent JavaScript APIs to improve browser support
  * Fix several styling issues on the challenge page

 -- Marko Zajc <marko@zajc.tel>  Wed, 25 Feb 2026 17:36:10 +0100

libnginx-mod-http-shapow (1.2) stable; urgency=high

  * Fix a severe regression in module reloading that would lead to unallocated
    memory access when reloading to a different bucket count
  * Use better log levels
  * Fix several smaller issues

 -- Marko Zajc <marko@zajc.tel>  Sun, 22 Feb 2026 16:26:37 +0100

libnginx-mod-http-shapow (1.1) stable; urgency=high

  * Fix a severe bug that could lead to bad memory reads due to asynchronous
    request handling
  * Fix a severe bug that prevented table pruning after ordinal overflow
  * Fix many bugs that could cause issues (including memory corruption) during
    or after a reload
  * Fix many other bugs and restrict potentially unsafe or problematic
    configuration

 -- Marko Zajc <marko@zajc.tel>  Sun, 22 Feb 2026 03:34:31 +0100

libnginx-mod-http-shapow (1.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.

 -- Marko Zajc <marko@zajc.tel>  Wed, 21 Feb 2026 03:34:50 +0100
